[{"id":16753084,"title":"AI Summer Discussion Club: Keeping the human in the loop","allday":false,"start":"2026-07-08T15:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-07-08T16:00:00-07:00","created":"2026-04-17T15:23:54-07:00","description":"<p data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Thinking about artificial intelligence this summer? Join our AI Summer Discussion Club in person at the FAMRI Library in Mission Bay! Each month, we will discuss 2-3 articles, videos, or news pieces about different AI topics.</p>\n\n<p>We will have tea and light snacks. Feel free to sign up for single sessions or all of them!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Upcoming:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>July 8 @ 3pm:</strong> Keeping the human in the loop</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>August 12 @ 3pm:</strong> Are we heading for AI dystopia? (<a href=\"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/16753085\">Register</a>)</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The reading/watching commitment for this series is relatively light (15-30 min of content), and discussion questions will be shared with registrants before the session. Reading/watching assigned content in advance and taking some notes is recommended, but not required for participation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>More information on assigned content for this session to be announced.</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Accessibility</strong></h3>\n\n<p>UCSF welcomes all participants to our events. If you need a reasonable accommodation to participate in this event because of a disability, please contact Eileen Chen at eileen.chen@ucsf.edu as soon as possible.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>People</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Eileen Chen</strong> is an Education and Research Librarian. She supports literature searching, AI, and open access publishing.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Geoff Boushey </strong>is a Data Science Specialist. He teaches with Python, SQL, machine learning, and AI, with an emphasis on document, text, and media analysis.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Yea-Hung Chen</strong> is a Data Science Specialist. He provides support on R, data science, and AI to the UCSF community.</li>\n</ul>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/16753084","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=16753084"},"location":"FAMRI Library","category":[{"id":86724,"name":"AI"},{"id":27094,"name":"Data Science"}],"owner":{"id":133839,"name":"Eileen Chen"},"presenter":"","calendar":{"id":928,"name":"Library Events and Classes","public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/calendar/events","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/admin/calendar/928"},"seats":50,"registration":true,"registration_form_id":0,"registration_series_linked":false,"has_registration_opened":true,"registration_open_at":"2026-04-17T15:23:54-07:00","has_registration_closed":false,"registration_close_at":"2026-07-08T15:00:00-07:00","physical_seats":50,"physical_seats_taken":23,"online_seats":0,"online_seats_taken":0,"seats_taken":23,"wait_list":false,"color":"#058488","featured_image":"","featured_image_alt_text":"","geolocation":null,"future_dates":[],"registration_cost":0,"more_info":"","setup_time":0,"teardown_time":0},{"id":15918953,"title":"Needlecraft Monthly Meet-Up - July","allday":false,"start":"2026-07-10T12:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-07-10T13:00:00-07:00","created":"2025-12-05T13:17:20-08:00","description":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana; font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img alt=\"makers lab logo\" src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/libapps/accounts/17525/images/MakersLabLogo-web.png\" style=\"width: 351px; height: 91px;\" /></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#e74c3c;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></strong></span><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Calling all fans of knitting, crochet, cross-stitch, sewing, and embroidery!</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">This virtual meet-up is a chance for beginning and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">experienced</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"> UCSF crafters&nbsp;to come together and work on their projects in a fun and relaxed atmosphere. We hang, we chat, we work on&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">fabulous&nbsp;projects, and share advice and inspiration. Join us! </span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Register below to receive the Zoom link and password. </strong>See all upcoming <a href=\"http://tiny.ucsf.edu/needlecraftmeetup\" target=\"_blank\">Needlecraft Meet-Ups</a> to save your seat today!</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">All Makers Lab pop-ups are open to the UCSF community. </span>If you are a DPH employee, UCSF alum or retiree, please&nbsp;<a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">contact the Makers Lab</a>&nbsp;to register for this pop-up.</span></p>\n\n<p><em>Photo from UCSF staff member Brenda</em></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Have questions about the Makers Lab?</strong> Visit the <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/use/makerslab/\" target=\"_self\">Makers Lab webpage</a> <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">or <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\" target=\"_self\">contact us</a></span></span></span>. <span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The Makers Lab is open by appointment for UCSF teaching, learning, and research projects. Contact the <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\">Makers Lab</a> to schedule an appointment. </span></span></span></p>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/15918953","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=15918953"},"location":"","campus":"Online","category":[{"id":25201,"name":"Makers Lab"},{"id":57276,"name":"Needlecraft"}],"owner":{"id":16958,"name":"UCSF Library Makers Lab"},"presenter":"Ariel Deardorff","calendar":{"id":928,"name":"Library Events and Classes","public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/calendar/events","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/admin/calendar/928"},"seats":12,"registration":true,"registration_form_id":16241,"registration_series_linked":false,"has_registration_opened":true,"registration_open_at":"2025-12-05T13:17:20-08:00","has_registration_closed":false,"registration_close_at":"2026-07-10T12:00:00-07:00","physical_seats":0,"physical_seats_taken":0,"online_seats":12,"online_seats_taken":8,"seats_taken":8,"wait_list":true,"color":"#EB093C","featured_image":"https://d68g328n4ug0e.cloudfront.net/data/feat_img/138/928/1764969430.jpg","featured_image_alt_text":"","geolocation":null,"future_dates":[],"registration_cost":0,"more_info":"","setup_time":0,"teardown_time":0,"online_user_id":0,"online_meeting_id":"","online_host_url":"","online_join_url":"https://ucsf.zoom.us/j/97547992565?pwd=ZmHNEuktXGHjDi7cTw7IkvL1KgyDrX.1&from=addon","online_join_password":"156180","online_provider":"external"},{"id":17049736,"title":"Leveraging Dimensions for Research Reporting","allday":false,"start":"2026-08-12T11:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-08-12T12:00:00-07:00","created":"2026-06-11T12:05:11-07:00","description":"<p dir=\"ltr\">Please join us for a training session tailored to UCSF&#39;s reporting needs. This session will be led by Caroline Crossman, Dimensions Engagement Manager, who will walk you through how to get the most out of Dimensions to support reports on research activity and impact. Topics will include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Reporting at the university level, using the Research Organization&nbsp;and additional filters to refine search results</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Reporting on research departments, institutes, and labs by creating custom Groups in Dimensions or by using the ID Search to explore a subset of publications specific to your group</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Exploring researcher profiles in Dimensions to assess research productivity and showcase research impact using citations and altmetrics&nbsp;</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Please note that this session will be recorded.</p>\n\n<h3>About Dimensions&nbsp;</h3>\n\n<p>Dimensions is a comprehensive research intelligence platform that connects publications, grants, clinical trials, patents, and policy documents in one place. With powerful search and analytics capabilities, it enables institutions, research groups, and individual researchers to track funding landscapes, measure research impact through citation and Altmetric data, and map collaborations.</p>\n\n<p>Find out more about <a href=\"https://guides.ucsf.edu/dimensions\">UCSF&#39;s access to Dimensions</a>, and access the application with your UCSF email address at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://app.dimensions.ai/\">app.dimensions.ai</a></p>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/17049736","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=17049736"},"location":"","campus":"Online","audience":[{"id":7980,"name":"Faculty"},{"id":7981,"name":"Staff"},{"id":7982,"name":"Students"},{"id":7983,"name":"Postdocs"}],"category":[{"id":409,"name":"Database and Searching"},{"id":37580,"name":"Education and Research"},{"id":33523,"name":"Scholarly Communication"}],"owner":{"id":3953,"name":"Anneliese Taylor"},"presenter":"C